<br>
couple things...<br>
the original keeps mid took over were not pc defended.  conquest went after them because they wanted to be the first to take over some keeps.  they got hibernia completely taken over and then took over a couple of ours and we decided hell no, we didn't feel like getting rolled when there was fun to be had defending.  <br>
<br>
during the first pc defended keep raid, we had about ten people inside the keep.  mids came up and those ten pc's kept them at bay long enough for the defenders to assemble and get to the keep under seige.  just barely though, they were fighting in the courtyard by the time the back up arrived.<br>
<br>
so far, every pc defended keep that has gone under seige has resulted in failed attempts.  it's fun as hell though.  <br>
<br>
if you have levels, taking an npc defended keep is cake.  even we can do it, and for awhile, albion was the weakest, furthest behind realm on merlin.  but we got spunk.  <br>
<br>
regarding the casual gamers..well, that one is easy.  if you are a crappy powergamer and level real fast and go out pvping, you'll harm your realm as much as any casual gamer could.  if you are a good casual gamer, you will aid the realm more than a crappy powergamer, and as much as a good one.  <br>
<br>
the way i see it is like this.  because there is a cap, everyone will eventually be on equal footing, right?  well, just because someone is a casual gamer does not mean they suck.  the flaw in all those analogies everyone is putting up is that there are extremes on both sides.  that is not the case in this game.  as was pointed out above.  casual gamer A B and C can go out with powergamers and be just as good as the opposing realm that are filled with powergamers...if the casuals are decent or the powers are not awful.  believe me, i see a lot of clueless powers in albion everyday...<br>
<br>
so instead of putting the marines on one side and the guard on the other, put a few guards in with one side and a few marines with the others.  leaders will naturally fall into place as the most experienced and capable, and it will be a more even fight.  that is daoc.<br>
<br>
kanya<br>
